Completed: *Add IP-conscious README intro* (1/2)

**Repo Description Draft (for GitHub)**

ColorLang is an experimental, machine-native programming framework that encodes executable instructions, data, UI state, and optional agent cognition as HSV color pixels inside a single image artifact. A spatial virtual machine decodes hue bands into opcode classes while saturation/value quantize operands. The repo demonstrates:

- Color-encoded instruction grids and a working VM
- Hybrid paletteâ†’RLE compression tailored to instruction tiles
- Visualization and debugging (program images, execution trace)
- React-style component rendering to color grids (ColorReact)
- Optional cognition strip for meta-state experiments
- Research planning (thesis, IP assessment, Phase 2 benchmarks)

Patent-Pending Concepts (under evaluation):
- Band-aware hue decoding + operand quantization
- Hybrid compression + deterministic rehydration
- Planned error-correction (ECC) and integrity (tile hashing/Merkle)
- Unified executable + UI + meta-state artifact

Trademarks (candidate): â€œColorLangâ€, â€œColorReactâ€ â„¢

IP Posture:
- Code here released under MIT (see License).
- Publication does not waive patent rights for unimplemented or withheld advanced techniques.
- Contributions imply you have rights and grant usage under MIT; refinements may inform future filings.

Watermarked PDFs (thesis, IP assessment, provisional outline) are under pdf.

Security & Integrity: Prototype only; do not rely for production. Please report vulnerabilities privately.

Use Cases:
- Research into visual/spatial program representations
- Rapid experimentation in color-encoded execution models
- Compression and robustness benchmarking for image-program artifacts
- UI/state visualization pipelines

Next Research Phase (planned):
- Corpus benchmarks vs PNG/WebP+zstd
- Integrity/ECC implementation
- Scale + GPU decode prototype

