**README Top Intro (replace first section header + lead paragraph)**
ColorLang: Machineâ€‘Native Colorâ€‘Encoded Programming (Patentâ€‘Pending Concepts)
ColorLang encodes executable instructions and data as HSV pixels in an image grid. Hue bands define opcode classes; saturation/value quantize operands. The image is the canonical artifact for execution, compression, and visualization. This repo shares open research code sufficient for validation while reserving certain implementation refinements pending IP filings.

- Patent status: See Provisional_Patent_Outline.md and watermarked PDFs under pdf. Publication here does not waive patent rights.
- Trademark notice: â€œColorLangâ€ and â€œColorReactâ€ are candidate marks (â„¢). Do not brand derivative products with these names without consent.
- Scope: Please experiment, benchmark, and share feedback. Avoid presenting derivative implementations as production â€œColorLangâ€ without attribution.
- Security: Prototype code. Donâ€™t process untrusted inputs.
- Contributions & IP: By contributing you affirm rights to contribute under the repo license and acknowledge contributions may inform future filings (youâ€™ll be credited).

